==身分區別==
[[File:Onepercenter Vest.svg|thumb|幫會背心的布章佈局及含意示例：<br/>
'''1''') 幫會名稱<br/>
'''2''') 幫會標誌 + 「MC」字樣<br/>
'''3''') 國家、洲、郡或城市<br/>
'''4''') 「1%」、「1%er」布章代表大型幫會<br/>
'''5''') 特殊頭銜、稱號、分會名稱<br/>
'''6''') 幫會銜級、職務<br/>
'''7''') 側面 – 地區分會名稱]]
早期的機車幫會通常是將牛仔夾克或皮夾克剪裁成背心，幫會背心的背面往往是用來辨識機車幫會的主要途徑，因為他們都會將幫派徽章縫在背面中央，這些識別布章除了幫派徽章還包括幫派名稱、堂口所在地和機車俱樂部的英文縮寫「MC」，以及國家、州、省，或其他分會地區的識別布章。許多平民俱樂部也會將背心縫上布章，例如{{link-en|哈雷車主俱樂部|Harley Owners Group}}，但他們不會縫上「MC」。

機車幫會的布章永遠是幫會本身的財產<ref name="nwherald">{{cite web|language=en|url=https://www.nwherald.com/2014/09/26/outlaws-motorcycle-club-seeks-patches-seized-in-wonder-lake-bar-fight-case/aboztrg/|title=Outlaws Motorcycle Club seeks patches seized in Wonder Lake bar fight case|publisher=Northwest Herald|accessdate=2020-06-30|date=2014-09-28|archive-date=2020-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702202311/https://www.nwherald.com/2014/09/26/outlaws-motorcycle-club-seeks-patches-seized-in-wonder-lake-bar-fight-case/aboztrg/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，雖然只有正式成員可以穿戴幫會的徽章，但這些布章的所有權並不屬於成員自己的。一個機車幫會的成員必須嚴謹保護自己的幫會背心，如果讓自己的幫會背心落入外人手中，就是一種非常恥辱的行為，可能會導致幫會成員喪失身分資格或遭到其他懲罰。通常一些規模較大的機車幫會會把幫派徽章註冊成商標，例如[[地獄天使_(幫會)|地獄天使]]在全世界五十多個國家將他們的死亡頭骨圖案註冊成商標，積極保護其幫會標誌，防止未經授權的使用<ref name="NYmongols">{{cite web|language=en|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/us/mongols-motorcycle-club-government.html|title=How to Crush an Outlaw Biker Club: Seize Its … Logo?|publisher=[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]|accessdate=2020-06-30|date=2018-11-21|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108100850/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/us/mongols-motorcycle-club-government.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="HowStuffWorks"/>。

===布章===
幫會布章的傳統源自於軍團旗、部隊隊徽、[[軍階|軍階]]和軍事獎章<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L3O1VUCsAgEC |title=The End of Internationalism: Or World Governance? |publisher=Praeger |first=J. Ørstrøm |last=Møller |date=2000 |isbn=0-275-96701-8 |access-date=2020-06-15 |archive-date=2020-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627023026/https://books.google.com/books?id=L3O1VUCsAgEC |dead-url=no }}</ref>。機車幫會之間的關係很複雜，在幫會背心上的布章主要用以標識其成員隸屬的幫會和領土位置<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NnQx2_586TAC |title=Cultural Criminology |publisher=Northeastern University Press |first1=Jeff |last1=Ferrell |first2=Clinton R. |last2=Sanders |date=1995 |isbn=978-1-55553-236-9 |access-date=2020-06-15 |archive-date=2020-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627023159/https://books.google.com/books?id=NnQx2_586TAC |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同時也能反映幫會文化中教派般的象徵，對他們來說如同國旗一樣神聖不可侵犯，並能提供配戴者的社會史，如前科、吸毒，以及其他效忠幫會的訊息<ref name="NYmongols"/><ref name="ncbi"/>。自1960年代以來，許多不同的機車幫會都穿著類似風格的布章。許多人認為它們是摩托車騎士中的精英象徵，其風格已被其他次文化廣泛複製並商業化<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=z4A22ycfZ0YC |title=Harley-Davidson and Philosophy: Full-Throttle Aristotle |publisher=Open Court |series=Popular Culture and Philosophy |volume=18 |editor1-first=Bernard E. |editor1-last=Rollin |editor2-first=Carolyn M. |editor2-last=Gray |editor3-first=Kerri |editor3-last=Mommer |editor4-first=Cynthia |editor4-last=Pineo |date=2006 |isbn=978-0-8126-9589-2 |access-date=2020-06-15 |archive-date=2020-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924023019/https://books.google.com/books?id=z4A22ycfZ0YC |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Schouten1995">{{cite journal |title=Subcultures of Consumption: An Ethnography of the New Biker |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-consumer-research_1995-06_22_1/page/43 |journal=Journal of Consumer Research |first1=John W. |last1=Schouten |first2=James H. |last2=McAlexander |volume=22 |issue=1 |pages=43-61 |date=June 1995 |doi=10.1086/209434 |jstor=2489699}}</ref>。背心上的布章是幫會成員「社交化的重要標誌」，展示自己在組織內的階級排名，並呈現一種主要的身份象徵，帶有相關的象徵意義<ref>{{cite journal |title=The Arts of the Motorcycle: Biology, Culture, and Aesthetics in Technological Choice |journal=Technology and Culture |first=Steven L. |last=Thompson |volume=41 |issue=1 |pages=99-115 |date=January 2000 |doi=10.1353/tech.2000.0040}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Leathers and Rolexs: The Symbolism and Values of the Motorcycle Club |journal=Deviant Behavior |first1=James F. |last1=Quinn |first2=Craig J. |last2=Forsyth |volume=30 |issue=3 |pages=235-265 |date=February 2009 |doi=10.1080/01639620802168700}}</ref>。如果醫生和醫務人員在急診室對機車幫會成員進行救治期間，應謹慎對待傷患的幫會背心，否則可能會遭受機車幫會的敵對反應<ref name="ncbi"/>。

大多數機車幫會成員布章的顏色會遵循慣例，具有與它們各自的標誌相關的兩種色調；例如地獄天使的布章都帶有紅色和白色、{{link-en|惡棍之徒機車俱樂部|Bandidos Motorcycle Club|惡棍之徒}}的布章都帶有紅色和黃色<ref name="ncbi"/>。絕大多數正式的幫會背心都是三片式布章；包括頂部的幫派名稱布章（top rocker）、中間的幫會標誌布章（rocker）和底部的堂口所在地布章（bottom rocker）<ref>{{cite web|language=en|title=We Asked a Bandido About the Biker Gangs' Leather Style Dispute|url=https://www.gq.com/story/bandidos-gang-leather-patch-style|work=[[GQ|GQ]]|date=2015-05-20|accessdate=2020-06-24|archive-date=2020-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201203083243/https://www.gq.com/story/bandidos-gang-leather-patch-style|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="HotCars3"/><ref name="HowStuffWorks">{{cite web|language=en|url=https://auto.howstuffworks.com/motorcycle-club-colors2.htm|title=What motorcycle club colors represent|publisher=HowStuffWorks|accessdate=2020-06-30|archive-date=2020-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026164259/https://auto.howstuffworks.com/motorcycle-club-colors2.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這些布章的形狀通常是弧形，布章的數量和安排有時是表明機車幫會的性質。雖然許多機車俱樂部也穿著三件式布章，但這並不一定表明該俱樂部是一個不法分子組成的機車幫會。政府的執法機構在突擊幫會、俱樂部或幫會成員的住宅時，會沒收這些機車幫會背心，他們經常在[[記者會|新聞發布會]]上展示這些物品<ref name=Bandidos>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060410/mass_murder_autopsies_060410 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060412135432/http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060410/mass_murder_autopsies_060410 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2006-04-12 |title=Five charged in murders of eight Bandidos bikers |website=CTV.ca |date=2006-06-10 |accessdate=2007-10-10 }}</ref>。這些衣物會被用於審判時的佐證，作為幫會成員代表其俱樂部進行犯罪行為的起訴聲明<ref>[[美國聯邦第七巡迴上訴法院|美國聯邦第七巡迴上訴法院]], Case Nos. 95-2829 and 95-2879; UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. JOHN E. IRVIN and THOMAS E. PASTOR, Defendants-Appellants</ref>。

===「MC」方塊、「1%」鑽石布章===
外界要辨識穿戴布章背心的人是否為幫會份子的途徑，除了帶有地名的三片式布章之外，「MC」方塊與「1%」鑽石布章也是判斷的方式之一。在機車幫會的世界中，「MC」字樣代表了機車俱樂部的英文縮寫，這種布章絕大多數是方塊狀<ref name="ncbi"/><ref name="HowStuffWorks"/>。每個機車幫會的布章都一定會有明顯「MC」字樣，這是為了確保任何人不會將他們與平民俱樂部混淆<ref name="HotCars24"/>。而「1%」和「1%er」布章全部都是鑽石形（菱形）的，代表配戴者隸屬於大型幫會。為了避免大型幫會的挑戰，一些獨立的、小規模的機車幫會不會配戴 「1%」布章，但這些次級幫會可能與大型的「1%」幫會一樣暴力。因此，缺少「1%」布章並不能排除配戴者與其隸屬幫會的犯罪程度或忠誠度<ref name="ncbi"/><ref name="HotCars24"/>。

===其他布章===
有一些機車幫會成員可能會擁有其他布章，包括短語和符號，以代表各種成就和象徵意義<ref name="HowStuffWorks"/>。這些其他布章的風格或意義在不同的機車幫會之間也有變化。例如人頭骨圖案、榮譽頭銜、紀念章或座右銘，特別是一些執行過謀殺或其他暴力行為的成員，經常會擁有和他人不同的特殊布章<ref>[http://www.ktla.com/content_landing_page/?Dozens-of-Mongols-Biker-Gang-Members-Arr=1&blockID=112738&feedID=171]{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} KTLA TV, Los Angeles</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.insidesocal.com/sgvcrime/Mongols_-_SW_affidavit%5B1%5D.pdf |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2009-08-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309104139/http://www.insidesocal.com/sgvcrime/Mongols_-_SW_affidavit%5B1%5D.pdf |archivedate=2012-03-09 }} ATF affidavit</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Hell's angels: a strange and terrible saga |first=Hunter S. |last=Thompson |publisher=Random House |year=1996 |isbn=0-345-41008-4 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oosssb76G9oC&pg=PA8 |accessdate=2017-06-29 |archive-date=2019-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823135636/https://books.google.com/books?id=oosssb76G9oC&pg=PA8 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Becker 1996 432">{{Citation |title=Criminal Investigation |first=Ronald |last=Becker |publisher=Jones & Bartlett Publishers |year=1996 |isbn=0-8342-1711-2 |page=第432頁 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tSyjRXt_qpEC&pg=PA432&lpg=PA432&dq=13+patch+marijuana+outlaw+motorcycle+gangs+site:books.google.com&q= |accessdate=2017-06-29 |archive-date=2020-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805053343/https://books.google.com/books?id=tSyjRXt_qpEC&pg=PA432&lpg=PA432&dq=13%20patch%20marijuana%20outlaw%20motorcycle%20gangs%20site%3Abooks.google.com&q= |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

另外還有「翅膀」或「機車翅膀」圖案的特殊布章，它們就像{{link-en|傘兵徽章|Parachutist Badge}}或{{link-en|飛行員徽章|Aviator badge}}那樣，但是具有各種顏色代碼的不同含義，例如據說在某些機車幫會，與患有[[性病|性病]]的女性發生過[[性關係|性關係]]的成員可能會縫著「綠翅膀」<ref name="Becker 1996 432"/><ref>[http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,24537495-663,00.html] {{Wayback|url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,24537495-663,00.html |date=20090530180636 }} Herald Sun</ref><ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/worldnews/article-1079665/Mongols-motorcycle-club-members-arrested-mass-California-swoop.html] Daily Mail</ref><ref>{{Citation |last=Glover |first=Scott |date=2008-10-22 |title=Raid targets Mongols motorcycle gang |newspaper=[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]] |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/oct/22/local/me-mongols22?pg=1 |quote=There also are patches associated with the gang's alleged sexual rituals. Members are awarded wings of varying colors for engaging in sex acts with women at pre-arranged 'wing parties,' the indictment states. For example, members who have sex with a woman with venereal disease are given green wings, according to the indictment. |accessdate=2017-06-29 |archive-date=2012-01-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111132346/http://articles.latimes.com/2008/oct/22/local/me-mongols22?pg=1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這些定義有時是一個惡作劇，目的是揶揄模仿機車幫會穿著的平民騎士，也是為了激怒保守的公眾和政府當局為目的<ref name=Bourne2007>{{Citation |title=Philosophical Ridings: Motorcycles and the Meaning of Life |last= Bourne |first= Craig |publisher= {{link-en|Oneworld Publications|Oneworld Publications}} |year= 2007 |isbn= 1-85168-520-0 |pages= 第11–12頁}}</ref>。通常，額外的布章都是符號，例如使用[[納粹|納粹]]標誌或[[親衛隊|親衛隊]]的死亡頭骨。這些一般不是用來表示同情納粹，而是用來表達機車幫會對社會限制的全面反對，並且希望震驚那些不了解騎士文化的人<ref>{{Citation |author=Pratt |first=Alan R. |chapter=Motorcycling, Nihilism, and the Price of Cool; Nihilism and FTW Style |editor-last=Rollin |editor-first=Bernard E. |year=2006 |title=Harley-Davidson and philosophy: full-throttle Aristotle; Volume 18 of Popular culture and philosophy |publisher=Open Court Publishing |isbn=9780812695953 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NrsfTreAPfwC&pg=PA82 |quote='Dangerous Motorcycle Gangs,' a widely circulated two-hour police course, notes that a white cross on a biker's colors is earned by robbing a grave, a red cross by 'committing homosexual fellatio with a witness present.' Green wings denote the wearer performed cunnilingus on a venereally diseased woman and purple wing signify—get this!—oral sex with a dead woman! (第32頁). As a rejection of values and an expression of nihilism, what could be more aberrant and grossly offensive? And even if these interpretations are inaccurate or fabricated by bikers themselves as a joke, they still reveal the outrage that the outlaw biker expression of nihilism intended to inspire. |accessdate=2017-06-29 |archive-date=2020-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804101009/https://books.google.com/books?id=NrsfTreAPfwC&pg=PA82 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?ei=WTuuT4nGKNTs8QPNyeHQCQ&id=_5q3AoSbTGAC&dq=hells+angels&q=hells+angels#v=snippet&q=hells%20angels&f=false |title=Ebony Dec 1966 |publisher=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-11-12 |archive-date=2020-09-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200901034445/https://books.google.com/books?ei=WTuuT4nGKNTs8QPNyeHQCQ&id=_5q3AoSbTGAC&dq=hells+angels&q=hells+angels#v=snippet&q=hells%20angels&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
